         For the sake of the young necro's who read this, I will respond so they will not be misled by the lies of Potus and the like.</P><P>But first, regarding enchanters:<BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> I have to disagree here, one unresistable tash, mez, mana tap, nuke, mez, nuke, mez, nuke, death. While enchanters are killable, they can be very formidable too.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>This is about what the knowledge level of Potus is too. Anyone who thinks enchanters arev "very formidable", is just showing how clueless he is. For an enchanter, it takes great skill to be even the least bit effective in PvP. The best PvP chanter I have seen is on VZ is Vahmpir, what with him killing level 60 monks/rogues. You know how he was doing it? This tash-mez-nuke bullshit doesn't work. You have to understand, that an enchanter will NEVER be able to nuke a decent melee to death. Plus with some people now (read: Hardalek) exploiting like crazy and becoming un-mezzable, mez is becoming much less of an option as well.</P><P>Anyway, on to necro PvP...</P><P>Let's take apart what Potus said:<BR>DoT's: Right, the poison/disease based will be resisted. Splurt and FP and Vexing will NOT be resisted. You say they are too slow? You are an idiot. You say they will be dispelled? Do you realize that you can cast them AGAIN? --or-- How about starting off with Heat Blood? And then casting Vexing? Or if it's a melee just keep casting Heat until they run out of charges? You do realize that pumice and golem wands have charges, right? They can only dispell so many times.</P><P>And about the pets, forget them, we don't need them. But if we DO have a pet up, it's only to our advantage. You know what the pet is for? INTERRUPTS. That's right, no caster in his right mind would try to kill you without doing something about your pet first, wether it be rooting/mezzing/fearing/snaring it. You know what that means? That means you have TIME, which gives you the advantage. While they are busy casting on your pet, you are busy casting on them.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote> No dotting is wise at all, as they either take too long to cast, resist easily, and just get pumiced.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Wow.... that right there reached a new level of stupidity and cluelesness about necro PvP. I suppose next you're going to say that it's pointless for a melee to try to hit anyone because they'll just run around and heal up?</P><P>So basically you are a Necro who is trying to play like a Wizard. You say keep moving. Well DUH. You say only use lifetaps, I say why don't you go start a wizard, and let us smart Necro's stick with our 2k DoT's, mmmkay? mmkay</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Necros cannot win, as in the 3 seconds you claw and fight and beg for to lifetap a pathetic 200 dmg spell, the tank EASILY hits for more than that, for 0 mana, instantly, also chancing to interrupt you.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Yep, that's right dude -- YOU suck. Not the Necro's, only you, because you are so damn stupid. Lifetaps are used when? In an emergency or to finish somebody off. But then again, you wouldn't know that.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Shamans will kill you(Malo OWNS).<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Pray tell, what is a shaman going to do, MALO you to death?</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Clerics outheal you.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Only if you let them, which of course, being the stupid moron you are, you will.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Wizards and Mages have PvP worthy Epics. Our Epic is garbage in pvp, their's is rather nice.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Right, do you remember that Pumice stones have no class restriction on them? That's right -- Necro's can DISPELL wizard's epic. Of course, any smart necro wouldn't bother, because all he has to do is dot the wizard, and if the wizard starts dispelling himself, he'll dispell his own epic. By the way, do you realize that Vexing is a dot and not a DD? That's right -- eats right through their epic.</P><P>Mage epic -- a joke.</P><P>To all you idiots out there who scream pumice/golem: These things have charges, and are not unlimited. The amout of times you can cast boil blood is unlimited.</P><P>Basically, you have to be one hell of a raving retard to say Necro's suck in PvP. Of course, we're not #1, that place can go to Pal/SK, but we are definetly in the top 3. At least we don't have it as bad as clerics and enchanters heh</P><P>Necro on Vallon Zek<BR>There is no cow level.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
