         Angrier, you have not proved a single point in any of your posts. All you seemed to do is needlessly attack Potus.</P><P>I'm glad that Potus already pointed out all of your mistakes. I didn't look forward to quoting and explaining the flaws of your entire lengthy post.</P><P>I can support what Scyzek says. It is not like pumice stones are lore or expensive, there is nothing preventing a player from carrying around 2 backpacks full of stones. In fact, I know people who carry around this many pumice stones in addition to the other charged items they have. Trying reach the bottom of your opponent's backpack by tossing your mana at them is a rediculous strategy.</P><P>I have fought with someone who understood how to counter our dots. Nothing would stick. They were either resisted or dispelled. A minor distraction was all that my dots and all of my mana I spend on those dots were able to accomplish. In fact, the only thing I expect from my dots in PvP is to provide a distraction. Against people who know how to counter our dots, I use splurt as an opening attack to force them to dispell and provide me with an opportunity to deal uncontested damage.</P><P>I have to reinforce the opposition to one of your points.<BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>By the way, do you realize that Vexing is a dot and not a DD?  <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>A necro relying on dots to kill a wizard is one dead necro. Any 50+ wizard can easily kill a necro before the necro's first dot reaches its 3rd tick. Wizards do not bother to dispell your dots until you are dead. Wizards are the most common random-PKs on my server. I have seen <i>many</i> wizard related deaths. Rarely does it take more than two wizard nukes to kill another caster. When it does take more than 2 nukes, don't worry, the wizard will have a lot more where that came from. This is why you have to kill a wizard as fast as possible to even give you a chance to win. Although lifetaps are our best chance at killing a wizard quickly, they will NOT heal you enough to change anything before the fight is over. It only takes about 15 seconds for a wizard to deal two nukes (will deal up to 2k total). In 15 seconds, what can you do? Cast 3 deluxes? 3 defluxes will deal 600 and decrease the wizard's output by 600(not considering wiz epic). The score is still 1400 to 600. Surely the next nuke will kill you, unless you have good HP gear, but you wont hold out forever. Also, most wizards will use their niegh-unresistable stunnuke intermitently between their meatier nukes. This screws us up pretty bad. Most of our spells take a long time to cast, giving the wizard a lot of opportunies to make you "waste" your cast time.</P><P>Like I said before, it is possible for us kill any type of class. Sure. But we <i>ARE</i> at a disadvantage with most classes when our opponent plays with skill.</P><P>Rahant<BR>55th Boner<BR>Rallos Zek Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
