, and just get pumiced.<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------</P><P><BR>Wow.... that right there reached a new level of stupidity and cluelesness about necro PvP. I suppose next you're going to say that it's pointless for a melee to try to hit anyone because they'll just run around and heal up?</P><P>So basically you are a Necro who is trying to play like a Wizard. You say keep moving. Well DUH. You say only use lifetaps, I say why don't you go start a wizard, and let us smart Necro's stick with our 2k DoT's, mmmkay? mmkay<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>You stupid asschimp, Funeral Pyre can be pumiced off. What part of that you DON'T UNDERSTAND?  Are your referring to some kind of mystery DoT that does 2k full damage and can't be dispelled that only you know about? Maybe you should hit the ol cancel button and quit EQ.</P><P><BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>quote:<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Necros cannot win, as in the 3 seconds you claw and fight and beg for to lifetap a pathetic 200 dmg spell, the tank EASILY hits for more than that, for 0 mana, instantly, also chancing to interrupt you.<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------</P><P><BR>Yep, that's right dude -- YOU suck. Not the Necro's, only you, because you are so damn stupid. Lifetaps are used when? In an emergency or to finish somebody off. But then again, you wouldn't know that.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>So when you see your DoTs getting resisted and/or dispelled by a melee class then what spell are you going to use? In your case it would be G-A-T-E.</P><P><BR><BLOCKQUOTE id