GES. As for fighting a Wizard, I thought you said that we should be using Vex and Taps in emergencies or to finish off somebody. Does anybody other than me find Angrier clairvoyance amazing. He some how seem to know what everybody is going to do. (Besides, the wizard isn't going to be busy nuking you -- he's going to be busy trying to dispel the dots you landed on him) It's a freakin miracle how he knew that.</P><P><BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>quote:<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Come kill my 3k hp warrior with boil blood!<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------</P><P><BR>Why Boil Blood? Oh that's right, the point of my post was lost on you. I said cast Boil Blood in hopes of them wasting charges to dispel it.</P><P><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Lucky for us that melees can't read just like you. If they could they would have seen what the message was when the DoT landed on them.</P><P></P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>quote:<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>Vexing and ToN will have you OOM in no time flat<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------</P><P><BR>That's right -- that's why idiots like you who use only those spells are getting their asses kicked.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Ok loser, which way is it? Should we use ToN and Vex for emergencies and to finish off people or should we use them as part of our offensive arsenal? You can't seem to make up your mind when to use them.</P><P>Well champ go 